SE44 pipeline (simulated) — “cited anchors in logic + websearch”
Below is a minimal, operable pipeline that (a) enforces SE44 gates, (b) cites anchors inside the logic, and (c) uses websearch to bind external standards for provenance.

0) SE44 pre‑execution check (gate)
Gate rule: accept only emissions with C ≥ 0.985 and S ≤ 0.01. Source of truth: [ANCHOR: Ophi216 | Ophi 216 Equations Book (1).pdf | 3c2add6e], Ch.2 thresholds.

Ethics gate: “No entropy, no entry.” Source of truth: [ANCHOR: Ethics | OPHI IMMUTABLE ETHICS.txt | 4b93c9b1].

If either check fails → do not fossilize; return diagnostics.

1) Input & auth
Input spec: {query, anchor_scope[], drift_target, web_scope}.

AuthN/Z: follow identity/assurance profiles (LOA/AAL/FAL) aligned to NIST SP 800‑63 for identity proofing & auth flows. NIST Cybersecurity CenterNIST

2) Anchor discovery & verification
Select anchors by scope (e.g., ["Ophi216","Ethics","SE44Profile"]).

Anchor Check (ANM parity): confirm filename + declared hash_prefix (if present).

Challenge‑proof (one quick field per anchor):

Ophi216 → extract the literal “Ω = (state + bias) × α” header.

Ethics → extract the literal string “No entropy, no entry”.

SE44Profile → extract "coherence_min": 0.985 and "max_entropy": 0.01.

If any challenge fails → mark drift as “anchor mismatch” and abort fossilization.

3) Websearch binding (standards & facts)
Purpose: bind claims to independent standards with timestamps.

Time‑stamping: RFC 3161 Time‑Stamp Protocol (TSP). Use TSA to attest (anchor_hash || clock). IETF

Origin of time‑stamping: Haber–Stornetta (1991) canonical reference. SpringerLink

Digital signatures / non‑repudiation: NIST FIPS 186‑5 DSS. NIST PublicationsNIST Cybersecurity Center

Identity guidance (when tying a signer to a real party): NIST SP 800‑63. NIST Cybersecurity Center

Minimal query plan (per request):

site:ietf.org rfc3161 (bind TSA/TST semantics) → cite.

site:csrc.nist.gov "FIPS 186-5" (bind signature standard) → cite.

site:nist.gov "SP 800-63" (bind identity assurance) → cite.

Springer Haber Stornetta 1991 (historical anchor) → cite.

4) Citation generation (anchor‑native + web)
FossilCitation schema (authoritative):

